# Accessibility Standards

- WCAG 2.2 Level AA; ADA-aligned
- Semantic HTML first (`main`, `nav`, `form`, `label`, `button`, `input`)
- ARIA only when native semantics insufficient
- Keyboard: logical tab order, visible focus, Enter/Space for buttons, Escape for overlays
- Forms: every input has `<label>`; `aria-describedby` for errors, `aria-invalid` when invalid
- Images: meaningful `alt`; decorative use `alt=""`

```tsx
// Good: Label + error association
<label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
<input
  id="email"
  type="email"
  aria-describedby={error ? "email-error" : undefined}
  aria-invalid={!!error}
/>
{error && <span id="email-error" role="alert">{error}</span>}
```
